    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left, many have been trimmed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: Chiefly 13 lines in two columns; sometimes the short lines are centered; extensive marginalia.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Illuminated headpiece in gold and blue (f. 1v); textblock border-ruled in blue and gold; small flowers in gold with blue dots and red centers appear on the ends of short lines; stenciled designed in red and black (f. 5v-6r, 55v-56r); gold rulings between the columns and sections of poetry.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Binding: Bound in leather with plain paper sides over pasteboard, with flap (Type II); spine and fore-edge flap hinge are red leather</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: The item is not dated, but an owner's stamp places it before 1056 A.H., according to Simsar.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
